---
title: Alert
---

p.-text Alert messages provide contextual feedback for user actions.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | To render an alert, use the class <code>m-alert</code>.
  | A contextual class (e.g. <code>-warning</code>) is required to provide proper styling.

h4 Base
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    each type in ['success', 'danger', 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']
      .m-alert.-bubble.-m2(class=`-${type}`)
        = `This is a ${type} alert`
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -success" role="alert">This is a success alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -danger" role="alert">This is a danger alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -warning" role="alert">This is a warning alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -info" role="alert">This is an info alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -light" role="alert">This is a light alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -dark" role="alert">This is a dark alert</div>

h4 Icons
p.-text Use icons to provide additional clarity. Icons can be added to any alert by applying the class <code>-hasIcon</code>
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    each type in ['success', 'danger', 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']
      .m-alert.-bubble.-hasIcon.-m2(class=`-${type}`)
        = `This is a ${type} alert`
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -success -hasIcon" role="alert">This is a success alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -danger -hasIcon" role="alert">This is a danger alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -warning -hasIcon" role="alert">This is a warning alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -info -hasIcon" role="alert">This is an info alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -light -hasIcon" role="alert">This is a light alert</div>
      <div class="m-alert -dark -hasIcon" role="alert">This is a dark alert</div>

h5 Icon Center
p.-text Use the class <code>-iconCenter</code> to center the icons.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-hasIcon.-m2.-iconCenter(class=`-info`)
      = `Info alert with centered icon`
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -bubble -hasIcon -iconCenter -info" role="alert">Info alert with centered icon</div>

h4 Titled
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-danger.-hasIcon.-m2(data-title="Danger")
      | This is a danger alert
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -danger -hasIcon" data-title="Danger" role="alert">
        This is a danger alert
      </div>

h4 Dismissible
p.-text A button can be added to allow the user to dismiss the alert.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-warning.-hasIcon.-m2(data-title="Warning")
      | This is a warning alert
      button(class='a-btn -icon -close -small')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -warning -hasIcon" data-title="Warning" role="alert">
        This is a warning alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>

h4 Sizes
h5 Large
p.-text Apply a <code>-large</code> class to increase the size of the alert.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-warning.-large.-hasIcon.-m2(data-title="Warning")
      | This is a warning alert
      button(class='a-btn -icon -close -small')
        .a-btn__content
          i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -warning -large -hasIcon" data-title="Warning" role="alert">
        This is a warning alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
h3 Additional alert types
h4 Banner
p.-text
  | For alerts that stretch the full length of the page, apply the class <code>-banner</code>.
  | This will remove the border-left, border-right, and border-radius from the alert.
  | Banner alerts are commonly used to remind new users to confirm their email address or notify users
  | when they are experiencing connectivity issues.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-banner.-small.-success.-hasIcon.-m2
      | This is a success alert
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -banner -small -success -hasIcon" role="alert">
        This is a success alert
      </div>
h4 Toast
p.-text
  | Toasts are unobtrusive alerts used to display brief, auto-expiring information.
  | To use a toast alert, apply the class <code>-toast</code> and ensure the alert
  | is placed in the top right corner or bottom left corner of the screen.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    each type in ['success', 'danger', 'warning', 'info', 'light', 'dark']
      .m-alert.-toast.-hasIcon.-m2(class=`-${type}`, data-title=`${type}`)
        = `This is a ${type} alert`
        button(class='a-btn -icon -close -small')
          .a-btn__content
            i.a-icon.icon-x
  :code(lang="html")
      <div class="m-alert -toast -success -hasIcon" data-title="Success" role="alert">
        This is a success alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="m-alert -toast -danger -hasIcon" data-title="Danger" role="alert">
        This is a danger alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="m-alert -toast -warning -hasIcon" data-title="Warning" role="alert">
        This is a warning alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="m-alert -toast -info -hasIcon" data-title="Info" role="alert">
        This is an info alert
        <button class="a-btn -icon -close -small">
          <div class="a-btn__content">
            <i class="a-icon icon-x"></i>
          </div>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="m-alert -toast -light -hasIcon" data-title="Light" role="alert">
        This is a light alert
